                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-169-off904 t18280410-169-crimeloc907"></join>. On the 7th of March I was in the yard between twelve and one o'clock; I saw the prisoner loitering about the gate for half an hour; I watched him, and saw him take this plank of Spanish mahogany; he took it outside, set it down, and ran down Bunhill-row; our porter followed him, and I fetched the plank in.</p>
